  "prompt": "How much time it would take to get license from barrackpore rto?",
  "response": "The time it takes to get a driving license from the Barrackpore RTO (Regional Transport Office) can vary depending on several factors:\n\n1. Type of license (learner's permit, permanent license)\n2. Completeness of documentation\n3. Current workload at the RTO\n4. Whether you're applying for a new license or renewal\n\nTypically, the process might take:\n- Learner's License: 7-15 working days\n- Permanent License: 15-30 working days\n\nTo get an accurate and current timeline, I recommend:\n- Directly contacting Barrackpore RTO\n- Checking their official website\n- Visiting the RTO in person for precise information\n\nDocuments usually required:\n- Proof of age\n- Address proof\n- Medical certificate\n- Passport size photographs\n- Completed application form\n\nNote: Processing times can change, so it's best to verify current timelines with the RTO directly.",
